  <mainDescription>Whether you choose to keep and maintain two models - a Business Analysis Model and a Business Design Model - depend on a&#xD;
number of considerations: if the Business Analysis Model is retained, must be maintained along side the Business Design&#xD;
Model - and this is costly.&amp;nbsp; If the business is stable, then the Business Analysis Model is useful because it allows&#xD;
technology decisions, which do not affect the more abstract business structure, to be revisited more easily.&amp;nbsp; If there&#xD;
is high organizational or functional churn - there&amp;nbsp;might be less value, because the essence of the business changes&#xD;
and you need a new Business Analysis Model anyway.</mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
